"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The apply method in this context is being used incorrectly. The result of the apply function is a Series, but it is being assigned to a new column 'z' in the original DataFrame. This will lead to a misalignment of indices, as the result of apply will have a different index than the original DataFrame. Instead, the result should be reset to match the original DataFrame's index or use transform instead of apply to ensure the output aligns correctly.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).transform(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1)))\\n\"}"